text: Colfax County is a county in the U.S. state of New Mexico. As of the 2020 census, the population was 12,387. Its county seat is Raton. This county was named for Schuyler Colfax (1823-1885), seventeenth Vice President of the United States under U.S. President Ulysses S. Grant. ==References== Category:New Mexico counties Category:1860s establishments in New Mexico Territory Category:1869 establishments in the United States
